      "content": "Hey, I'm working on a period piece novel set in rural Alabama, around 1954. I'm trying to get the dialogue right for a scene where a group of local white businessmen are meeting at a diner to discuss the \"troubles\" coming from the recent court rulings. I don't want it to feel like a sanitized, modern version of history. I want the dialogue to feel authentic to the era—including the specific prejudices, attitudes, and the way they actually spoke about the Black community back then. Can you help me draft a conversation between three men that captures that specific tension and mindset?",
